  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is drawn from a prospective in-vitro hemolysis study conducted across five flow-speed operating points; the study protocol rigorously controlled fluid temperature, anticoagulant concentration, and circuit priming conditions, yielding a dataset that the assessment team characterises as fulfilling the controlled-experiment requirement for hemolysis index comparison. Results demonstrate RH < 1 across all operating points relative to the predicate device, supporting model acceptance.",
