    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for MRL 2. The six non-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 4. CFD predictions of NIH agree with in-vitro measurements within ±15% across all five operating points, and RH < 1 is confirmed for all conditions relative to the predicate device. The validation evidence, drawn from a structured in-vitro hemolysis monitoring study conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under CPB-relevant conditions, is considered sufficient to support model acceptance for the stated COU. The assessment team is satisfied that the experimental dataset provides a rigorous empirical basis for the hemolysis credibility argument and that the overall evidence package supports the Accepted decision.",
